subject: Re: [junit] need help
msgSnippet: ... Possibly. I tend to use Equals by reflex. Since Class apparently doesn t over-ride .equals(), it all comes out in the wash. -- Chris electric hedgehog
messageBody:
On Tuesday 22 March 2005 02:28, Robert Wenner wrote:
> On Monday 21 March 2005 09:07, Chris Dollin wrote:
> > On Monday 21 March 2005 10:46, sadia zai wrote:
> > > i want to test the types of two objects are same or not ,,
> > > how can i do dis
> >
> > (guessing)
> >
> > assertEquals( O1.getClass(), O2.getClass() );
>
> Take care, he probably wants just == or !=.
> Or, as it comes to assertions, assertSame.

Possibly. I tend to use Equals by reflex. Since Class apparently
doesn't over-ride .equals(), it all comes out in the wash.

--
Chris "electric hedgehog" Dollin
